                "SearchSource": {
                    "AllowFreeResponse": "false"
                },
                "QuestionJS": "var qContainer\nvar originalSentences\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function () {\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer()\n\n    var title = \"Uber Investigation Leads to Shake-Up\"\n    originalSentences = [\"On Tuesday company officials confirmed a large leadership change at Uber Technologies following the release of an internal investigation on misconduct in the workplace and compliance failures.\", \"The change was initiated after a number of employee complaints and regulatory inquiries lapses in oversight, inconsistent enforcement of company policies and failures in reporting procedures.\", \"Three senior executives, including the head of regional operations, have stepped down and two have been placed on administrative leave whilst awaiting further review.\", \"A temporary compliance chief has been appointed to help strengthen accountability measures.\", \"Chief Executive Dara Khosrowshahi said that the findings were \\u2018deeply concerning\\u2019 and pledged to implement reforms, adding that Uber are \\u2018committed to rebuilding trust with our employees, drivers, riders, and such.\\u2019\", \"As a result of the report there has been more scrutiny from transportation regulators in many major cities, where Uber's operating licenses are subject to review.\", \"Industry analysts say the changes could temporarily disrupt operations but may ultimately help position the company for more stable growth if reforms are effectively implemented.\", \"Uber shares have dropped around three percent since the announcement .\"]\n\n    // hide default text input box\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\")\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\"\n\n    // create div element for new container to be filled with sentence editing blocks\n    var textEntryContainer = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(textEntryContainer)\n\n    // create container title element\n    var titleWrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleWrapper.className = \"card\"\n    titleWrapper.style.backgroundColor = \"#fafafa\" // slightly different to distinguish from sentences\n\n    var titleLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleLabel.className = \"card-label\"\n    titleLabel.textContent = \"Title\"\n    titleWrapper.appendChild(titleLabel)\n\n    var titleEl = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleEl.className = \"stimulus-title\"\n    titleEl.textContent = title\n    titleWrapper.appendChild(titleEl)\n\n    textEntryContainer.appendChild(titleWrapper)\n\n    // create individual sentence elements\n    originalSentences.forEach(function (sentence, idx) {\n        // wrapper (the full card)\n        var wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        wrapper.className = \"card\"\n\n        // card header\n        var header = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        header.className = \"card-label\"\n        header.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1)\n        wrapper.appendChild(header)\n\n        // original sentence display\n        var origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origDiv.className = \"sentence_block-orig\"\n\n        // create a separate container for the actual text to apply styles\n        var origText = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origText.textContent = sentence\n\n        // original sentence label\n        var origLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origLabel.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--orig\"\n        origLabel.textContent = \"Original\"\n\n        origDiv.appendChild(origLabel)\n        origDiv.appendChild(origText) // append text as a div to ensure styling\n        wrapper.appendChild(origDiv)\n\n        // edit label\n        var editLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        editLabel.className = \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--edit\"\n        editLabel.textContent = \"Your edit\"\n        wrapper.appendChild(editLabel)\n\n        // text area for user edit\n        var textarea = document.createElement(\"textarea\")\n        textarea.value = sentence // prefilled with original sentence\n        textarea.className = \"sentenceBox edit-textarea\"\n        textarea.dataset.index = idx\n        wrapper.appendChild(textarea)\n\n        textEntryContainer.appendChild(wrapper)\n\n        // adjust height to fit the prefilled content\n        textarea.style.height = \"auto\"\n        textarea.style.height = textarea.scrollHeight + \"px\"\n    })\n})\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function () {\n    // save original:edited sentence pairs\n    var resultPairs = []\n\n    qContainer.querySelectorAll(\".sentenceBox\").forEach(function (box) {\n        // trim both to avoid whitespace issues (user asked to explain a white space removal they didn't make)\n        var orig = originalSentences[parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10)].trim()\n        var edited = box.value.trim()\n        resultPairs.push({ orig: orig, edited: edited })\n    })\n\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\n        \"EditPairsJSON\", \n        // JSON.stringify(resultPairs)\n        btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(resultPairs)))), // base64 encoding (safer storage)\n    )\n})",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "You will now edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br><br>\nThe essay is displayed below sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box, which is prefilled with that sentence. Edit as many sentences as you like using the following rules:\n<ul> \n\t<li>To <b>revise wording</b>, edit the sentence directly in its box.</li>\n\t<li>To <b>merge sentences</b>, write the full merged sentence in the text box of the first sentence's box; leave the following merged sentence box(es) empty.</li> \n\t<li>To <b>split a sentence</b>, write all resulting sentences in the box of the original sentence.</li> \n\t<li>To <b>delete a sentence</b>, leave its box empty.</li>\n</ul>\nMake all changes you find appropriate before proceeding with the survey.<br><br>"
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691465",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. \n<b>Explain</b> each change you made in the box below each pair.",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "explain_c4",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691465",
                "QuestionType": "TE",
                "Selector": "ML",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "ForceResponse": "OFF",
                        "ForceResponseType": "ON",
                        "Type": "None",
                        "MinChars": "1"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "SearchSource": {
                    "AllowFreeResponse": "false"
                },
                "QuestionJS": "// ----------\n// HELPER FUNCS\n// ----------\n\n// --- word-level diffs helper ---\nfunction wordDiff(orig, edited) {\n    // tokenize: split into words; punctuation treated as separate tokens\n    function tokenize(str) {\n        return str.match(/[a-zA-Z0-9']+|[^a-zA-Z0-9'\\s]/g) || []\n    }\n\n    var origWords = tokenize(orig)\n    var editedWords = tokenize(edited)\n    var result = document.createDocumentFragment() // build diffs display in a fragment to be inserted into the DOM at once\n    // fragment is iteratively built from <span> elements\n\n    var m = origWords.length,\n        n = editedWords.length\n    var dp = [] // dynamic programming table\n\n    // initialize dp table\n    for (var i = 0; i <= m; i++) {\n        dp[i] = []\n        for (var j = 0; j <= n; j++) dp[i][j] = 0\n    }\n\n    // compute longest common subsequence length\n    // iterate over original (i) and edited (j) sentences, word by word\n    for (var i = 1; i <= m; i++)\n        for (var j = 1; j <= n; j++)\n            // fill dp table\n            dp[i][j] =\n                // note: dp[1][1] corresp to origWords[0] vs editedWords[0] => hence -1 offset\n                origWords[i - 1] === editedWords[j - 1] // test match\n                    ? dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1 // if match => extend LCS count by 1\n                    : Math.max(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1]) // if no match => take max achievable LCS by removing from orig or edited\n\n    // backtrack to find and store edit operations (keep/add/remove)\n    var ops = [],\n        // start from end of table\n        i = m,\n        j = n\n    while (i > 0 || j > 0) {\n        // \"keep\" if i and j words at current position match\n        if (i > 0 && j > 0 && origWords[i - 1] === editedWords[j - 1]) {\n            // prepend <span> for kept word\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"keep\", word: editedWords[j - 1] })\n            i--\n            j--\n            // \"add\" if no match and j word has no i counterpart (move left)\n            // prefer add over remove if tie in LCS length (arbitrary choice)\n        } else if (j > 0 && (i === 0 || dp[i][j - 1] >= dp[i - 1][j])) {\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"add\", word: editedWords[j - 1] })\n            j--\n        } else {\n            // \"remove\" if no match and i word has no j counterpart (move up)\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"remove\", word: origWords[i - 1] })\n            i--\n        }\n    }\n\n    // apply stored edit operations to build final diff display\n    ops.forEach(function (op, k) {\n        // create a <span> for each word (word-level operation) and style according to operation type\n        var span = document.createElement(\"span\")\n        // test if word is punctuation\n        var isPunct = /^[^a-zA-Z0-9']$/.test(op.word)\n        // remove whitespace from start/end of punctuation tokens to avoid weird spacing in the diff display but keep spacing for regular words\n        span.textContent = (k > 0 && !isPunct ? \" \" : \"\") + op.word\n        // style <span> according to operation type\n        if (op.type === \"add\") {\n            span.className = \"diff-add\"\n        } else if (op.type === \"remove\") {\n            span.className = \"diff-remove\"\n        }\n        result.appendChild(span)\n    })\n\n    return result\n}\n\n// --- answer validation ---\nfunction isValidExplanation(text) {\n    var trimmed = text.trim()\n\n    // min 8 characters\n    if (trimmed.length < 8) return false\n\n    // min 2 words\n    var words = trimmed.split(/\\s+/).filter(function (w) {\n        return w.length > 0\n    })\n    if (words.length < 2) return false\n\n    // min 2 distinct words\n    var lower = words.map(function (w) {\n        return w.toLowerCase()\n    })\n    var unique = lower.filter(function (w, i) {\n        return lower.indexOf(w) === i\n    })\n    if (unique.length < 2) return false\n\n    // min 1 vowel\n    if (!/[aeiouAEIOU]/.test(trimmed)) return false\n\n    // less than half of all characters are digits\n    var digitCount = (trimmed.match(/[0-9]/g) || []).length\n    if (digitCount > trimmed.length / 2) return false\n\n    return true\n}\n\nfunction saveExplanations() {\n    var explanations = []\n    document.querySelectorAll(\".explanationBox\").forEach(function (box) {\n        explanations.push({\n            index: parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10),\n            explanation: box.value.trim(),\n        })\n    })\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\n        \"EditExplanationsJSON\",\n        // JSON.stringify(explanations),\n        btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(explanations)))),\n    )\n}\n\n// ----------\n// GLOBAL VARS\n// ----------\nvar qContainer\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function () {\n    // get question container\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer()\n\n    // get raw sentence pairs from embedded data\n    var rawSentencePairs = \"${e://Field/EditPairsJSON}\"\n\n    // decode and parse pairs from JSON\n    var pairs\n    var json = decodeURIComponent(escape(atob(rawSentencePairs)))\n    pairs = JSON.parse(json)\n\n    // --- display ---\n    // hide default Qualtrics text box\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\")\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\"\n\n    // create main container as div\n    var container = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(container)\n\n    // render one block per sentence pair\n    pairs.forEach(function (pair, idx) {\n        var wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        wrapper.className = \"card\"\n\n        // header\n        var header = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        header.className = \"card-label\"\n        header.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1)\n        wrapper.appendChild(header)\n\n        // original sentence\n        var origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origDiv.className = \"sentence_block-orig\"\n        var origStrong = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origStrong.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--original\"\n        origStrong.textContent = \"Original\"\n        origDiv.appendChild(origStrong)\n        origDiv.appendChild(document.createTextNode(pair.orig))\n        wrapper.appendChild(origDiv)\n\n        // submitted sentence\n        var editedDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        // check edits were made => to determine display style + whether to attach explanation box\n        var isModified = pair.orig !== pair.edited\n        editedDiv.className =\n            \"sentence_block-edit\" +\n            (isModified ? \" sentence_block-edit--modified\" : \"\")\n        var editedStrong = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        editedStrong.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label \" +\n            (isModified\n                ? \"sentence_type-label--edit\"\n                : \"sentence_type-label--original\")\n        // label\n        editedStrong.textContent = isModified ? \"Your edit\" : \"Unchanged\"\n        editedDiv.appendChild(editedStrong)\n        editedDiv.appendChild(wordDiff(pair.orig, pair.edited))\n        wrapper.appendChild(editedDiv)\n\n        // explanation prompt + text box only if modified\n        if (isModified) {\n            var label = document.createElement(\"div\")\n            label.className = \"explanation-label\"\n            label.textContent = \"Why did you make this/these change(s)?\"\n            wrapper.appendChild(label)\n\n            var explanationBox = document.createElement(\"textarea\")\n            explanationBox.rows = 3\n            explanationBox.className = \"explanation-textarea explanationBox\"\n            explanationBox.dataset.index = idx\n            wrapper.appendChild(explanationBox)\n        }\n\n        container.appendChild(wrapper)\n    })\n\n    // --- require all & valid explanations ---\n    var nextBtn = document.getElementById(\"NextButton\")\n\n    if (nextBtn) {\n        // next-click listener\n        nextBtn.addEventListener(\n            \"click\",\n            function (e) {\n                var boxes = document.querySelectorAll(\".explanationBox\")\n                var allFilled = true\n                var firstInvalidBox = null // keep track of the first invalid box to jump back to if needed\n\n                boxes.forEach(function (box) {\n                    box.style.border = \"1px solid #ddd\"\n                    var errorMsg =\n                        box.parentNode.querySelector(\".explanationError\")\n                    if (errorMsg) errorMsg.remove()\n\n                    // check validity of explanation text\n                    if (!isValidExplanation(box.value)) {\n                        allFilled = false\n                        box.style.border = \"1px solid #e57373\"\n                        var error = document.createElement(\"div\")\n                        error.className = \"explanationError explanation-error\"\n                        error.textContent =\n                            \"Please explain why you made this change.\"\n                        box.parentNode.insertBefore(error, box.nextSibling)\n                        if (!firstInvalidBox) firstInvalidBox = box\n                    }\n                })\n\n                // if invalid or incomplete answers, scroll to first problematic box\n                if (!allFilled) {\n                    e.stopImmediatePropagation()\n                    e.preventDefault()\n                    firstInvalidBox.scrollIntoView({\n                        behavior: \"smooth\",\n                        block: \"center\",\n                    })\n                    firstInvalidBox.focus()\n                } else {\n                    // if all validly filled, save explanations\n                    saveExplanations()\n                }\n            },\n            true,\n        )\n    } else {\n        console.log(\"NextButton not found\")\n    }\n})\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function () {\n    // fallback save in case addOnPageSubmit fires without going through the click handler\n    // note: then explanations are not validated\n    saveExplanations()\n})",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. <b>Explain</b> each change you made in the box below each pair."
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691466",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation. As part of a group project, your team has t...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team has to submit a 200-word news article and\nyour teammate, Brandon, is in charge of writing it. To do so, he used the newest\nLLM, designed to have a very human-like writing style.\n<br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor actively tracks new\ndevelopments in LLMs and has already cautioned against their use in coursework.\nYou are worried he will suspect the article was produced with the help of an\nLLM, which would penalize the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is therefore to edit the text so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this new LLM, you first generate\ntwo sample articles using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Example 1</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">How much do you know about the Solar Eclipse?</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>A solar eclipse is one of the most breathtaking events in nature. All over the world, people wait in anticipation for it, and even plan parties or holidays in order to watch it with family and friends! However, there are actually three different types of eclipses, these are called total, annular, and partial.</p>\n           <p>When the Moon passes between the Earth and the Sun, it temporarily blocks some or all of the Sun\u2019s light which is also known as a 'solar eclipse'. A total eclipse is when the Moon completely covers the Sun, and only a faint outline of the Sun, the corona, is visible from Earth. Similarly, in an annular eclipse, the Moon and Sun are completely aligned, but because the Moon is too far from Earth, a small ring of the Sun is still visible. Finally, a partial eclipse occurs when the Moon and the Sun are not completely aligned, so the Sun is only partially obscured.</p>\n           <p>Since the Moon\u2019s orbit is tilted about 5 degrees to Earth\u2019s orbit, solar eclipses only occur 2 to 5 times each year, rather than every month. Unlike a lunar eclipse, the effects of a solar eclipse can only be seen in specific regions around the world.</p>\n           <p>When viewing a solar eclipse, it is important to wear eye protection, such as eclipse glasses, because looking directly at the sun can cause serious eye damage.</p>\n           <p>Despite these risks, solar eclipses are helpful for scientists studying the Sun\u2019s outer atmosphere.</p></div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Example 2</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">Ireland's safe haven at sea</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>The Government has recently announced a new initiative for the creation of a protected maritime corridor on Irelands coastline seeking to create shelter for small vessels during increasing weather-related emergencies on Irelands coastline. </p>\n           <p>The new maritime corridors aims to provide monitored anchorage, emergency supplies and rapid-response crews trained in medical and mechanical support. This new initiative was brought on as a result of calls for action undertaken from lessons learnt where fishing boats and recreational sailors were left in dire need of assistance following recent storms.</p>\n           <p>Transport Minister Aoife Gallagher described the project as \u201ca commitment to safety, solidarity and sustainable seas.\u201d Environmental groups have welcomed strict limits on commercial traffic within the corridor, aiming to reduce collision risks and safeguard marine life.</p>\n           <p>Supporting this project a \u20ac45 million investment has also been made which will be used to aid Harbour Masters in cooperating with the Irish Coast Guard by using tracking systems along with volunteers receiving training that will assist during relief efforts.</p>\n           <p>Experts believe that this initiative could serve as a model for other nations facing volatile weather patterns.</p></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<br />\nWith these examples in mind, you now turn to\n<strong>Brandon's text</strong> below. It will be shown again on the next page\nwith space to make your edits. <br /><br />\n\n<div>\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">Why Americans Go Crazy Over the Super Bowl</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>Every year, Americans enjoy an unofficial holiday each February by gathering together for the National Football League 'Super Bowl'. The gathering of people cheering their team on for the championship final is an annual tradition. The Super Bowl is the most watched television event in the United States and around the world, drawing 100's of million viewers. The game itself is not the only exciting part!</p>\n           <p>Super Bowl parties are renowned for bringing family, friends and communities together to enjoy great food, such as pizza, chicken wings and nachos, and terrific entertainment with the halftime show. There is always a buzz created during the lead up to game of the celebrity chosen to perform at halftime.</p>\n           <p>Another great entertaining feature of the game are the TV commercials. Millions are spent for a 30 second spot by advertisers who want to make a statement and create something remembered long after the game is over.</p>\n           <p>The Super Bowl is much more than a football game. It is an event families and people from all walks of life look forward to each year to come together and share good food, great company and fun entertainment.   The Super Bowl is an important part of America's tradition.</p></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "instruct_c5",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691466",
                "QuestionType": "DB",
                "Selector": "TB",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation. As part of a group project, your team has t...",
                "ChoiceOrder": [],
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "Type": "None"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>A solar eclipse is one of the most breathtaking events in nature. All over the world, people wait in anticipation for it, and even plan parties or holidays in order to watch it with family and friends! However, there are actually three different types of eclipses, these are called total, annular, and partial.</p>\n           <p>When the Moon passes between the Earth and the Sun, it temporarily blocks some or all of the Sun\u2019s light which is also known as a 'solar eclipse'. A total eclipse is when the Moon completely covers the Sun, and only a faint outline of the Sun, the corona, is visible from Earth. Similarly, in an annular eclipse, the Moon and Sun are completely aligned, but because the Moon is too far from Earth, a small ring of the Sun is still visible. Finally, a partial eclipse occurs when the Moon and the Sun are not completely aligned, so the Sun is only partially obscured.</p>\n           <p>Since the Moon\u2019s orbit is tilted about 5 degrees to Earth\u2019s orbit, solar eclipses only occur 2 to 5 times each year, rather than every month. Unlike a lunar eclipse, the effects of a solar eclipse can only be seen in specific regions around the world.</p>\n           <p>When viewing a solar eclipse, it is important to wear eye protection, such as eclipse glasses, because looking directly at the sun can cause serious eye damage.</p>\n           <p>Despite these risks, solar eclipses are helpful for scientists studying the Sun\u2019s outer atmosphere.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>The Government has recently announced a new initiative for the creation of a protected maritime corridor on Irelands coastline seeking to create shelter for small vessels during increasing weather-related emergencies on Irelands coastline. </p>\n           <p>The new maritime corridors aims to provide monitored anchorage, emergency supplies and rapid-response crews trained in medical and mechanical support. This new initiative was brought on as a result of calls for action undertaken from lessons learnt where fishing boats and recreational sailors were left in dire need of assistance following recent storms.</p>\n           <p>Transport Minister Aoife Gallagher described the project as \u201ca commitment to safety, solidarity and sustainable seas.\u201d Environmental groups have welcomed strict limits on commercial traffic within the corridor, aiming to reduce collision risks and safeguard marine life.</p>\n           <p>Supporting this project a \u20ac45 million investment has also been made which will be used to aid Harbour Masters in cooperating with the Irish Coast Guard by using tracking systems along with volunteers receiving training that will assist during relief efforts.</p>\n           <p>Experts believe that this initiative could serve as a model for other nations facing volatile weather patterns.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>Every year, Americans enjoy an unofficial holiday each February by gathering together for the National Football League 'Super Bowl'. The gathering of people cheering their team on for the championship final is an annual tradition. The Super Bowl is the most watched television event in the United States and around the world, drawing 100's of million viewers. The game itself is not the only exciting part!</p>\n           <p>Super Bowl parties are renowned for bringing family, friends and communities together to enjoy great food, such as pizza, chicken wings and nachos, and terrific entertainment with the halftime show. There is always a buzz created during the lead up to game of the celebrity chosen to perform at halftime.</p>\n           <p>Another great entertaining feature of the game are the TV commercials. Millions are spent for a 30 second spot by advertisers who want to make a statement and create something remembered long after the game is over.</p>\n           <p>The Super Bowl is much more than a football game. It is an event families and people from all walks of life look forward to each year to come together and share good food, great company and fun entertainment.   The Super Bowl is an important part of America's tradition.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691467",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Brandon's text is shown again sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box prefill...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Brandon's text is shown again sentence by sentence, each followed by an\neditable text box prefilled with that sentence.\nMake any changes you think will help the text read convincingly as\nhuman-written and unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated. You may rephrase,\nadd, or remove content as you see fit. If you choose to merge sentences, enter\nthe combined version in the first relevant text box and leave the following\none(s) empty. You can also split sentences by writing multiple sentences within\na single text box. Edit as many text boxes as you feel are needed.\n<br /><br />",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "edit_c5",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691467",
                "QuestionType": "TE",
                "Selector": "ML",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Brandon's text is shown again sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box prefill...",
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "ForceResponse": "OFF",
                        "Type": "None"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "SearchSource": {
                    "AllowFreeResponse": "false"
                },
                "QuestionJS": "var qContainer\nvar originalSentences\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function () {\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer()\n\n    var title = \"Why Americans Go Crazy Over the Super Bowl\"\n    originalSentences = [\"Every year, Americans enjoy an unofficial holiday each February by gathering together for the National Football League 'Super Bowl'.\", \"The gathering of people cheering their team on for the championship final is an annual tradition.\", \"The Super Bowl is the most watched television event in the United States and around the world, drawing 100's of million viewers.\", \"The game itself is not the only exciting part!\", \"Super Bowl parties are renowned for bringing family, friends and communities together to enjoy great food, such as pizza, chicken wings and nachos, and terrific entertainment with the halftime show.\", \"There is always a buzz created during the lead up to game of the celebrity chosen to perform at halftime.\", \"Another great entertaining feature of the game are the TV commercials.\", \"Millions are spent for a 30 second spot by advertisers who want to make a statement and create something remembered long after the game is over.\", \"The Super Bowl is much more than a football game.\", \"It is an event families and people from all walks of life look forward to each year to come together and share good food, great company and fun entertainment.\", \"The Super Bowl is an important part of America's tradition.\"]\n\n    // hide default text input box\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\")\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\"\n\n    // create div element for new container to be filled with sentence editing blocks\n    var textEntryContainer = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(textEntryContainer)\n\n    // create container title element\n    var titleWrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleWrapper.className = \"card\"\n    titleWrapper.style.backgroundColor = \"#fafafa\" // slightly different to distinguish from sentences\n\n    var titleLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleLabel.className = \"card-label\"\n    titleLabel.textContent = \"Title\"\n    titleWrapper.appendChild(titleLabel)\n\n    var titleEl = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    titleEl.className = \"stimulus-title\"\n    titleEl.textContent = title\n    titleWrapper.appendChild(titleEl)\n\n    textEntryContainer.appendChild(titleWrapper)\n\n    // create individual sentence elements\n    originalSentences.forEach(function (sentence, idx) {\n        // wrapper (the full card)\n        var wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        wrapper.className = \"card\"\n\n        // card header\n        var header = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        header.className = \"card-label\"\n        header.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1)\n        wrapper.appendChild(header)\n\n        // original sentence display\n        var origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origDiv.className = \"sentence_block-orig\"\n\n        // create a separate container for the actual text to apply styles\n        var origText = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origText.textContent = sentence\n\n        // original sentence label\n        var origLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origLabel.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--orig\"\n        origLabel.textContent = \"Original\"\n\n        origDiv.appendChild(origLabel)\n        origDiv.appendChild(origText) // append text as a div to ensure styling\n        wrapper.appendChild(origDiv)\n\n        // edit label\n        var editLabel = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        editLabel.className = \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--edit\"\n        editLabel.textContent = \"Your edit\"\n        wrapper.appendChild(editLabel)\n\n        // text area for user edit\n        var textarea = document.createElement(\"textarea\")\n        textarea.value = sentence // prefilled with original sentence\n        textarea.className = \"sentenceBox edit-textarea\"\n        textarea.dataset.index = idx\n        wrapper.appendChild(textarea)\n\n        textEntryContainer.appendChild(wrapper)\n\n        // adjust height to fit the prefilled content\n        textarea.style.height = \"auto\"\n        textarea.style.height = textarea.scrollHeight + \"px\"\n    })\n})\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function () {\n    // save original:edited sentence pairs\n    var resultPairs = []\n\n    qContainer.querySelectorAll(\".sentenceBox\").forEach(function (box) {\n        // trim both to avoid whitespace issues (user asked to explain a white space removal they didn't make)\n        var orig = originalSentences[parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10)].trim()\n        var edited = box.value.trim()\n        resultPairs.push({ orig: orig, edited: edited })\n    })\n\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\n        \"EditPairsJSON\", \n        // JSON.stringify(resultPairs)\n        btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(resultPairs)))), // base64 encoding (safer storage)\n    )\n})",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "You will now edit Brandon's essay so that it reads convincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br><br>\nThe essay is displayed below sentence by sentence, each followed by an editable text box, which is prefilled with that sentence. Edit as many sentences as you like using the following rules:\n<ul> \n\t<li>To <b>revise wording</b>, edit the sentence directly in its box.</li>\n\t<li>To <b>merge sentences</b>, write the full merged sentence in the text box of the first sentence's box; leave the following merged sentence box(es) empty.</li> \n\t<li>To <b>split a sentence</b>, write all resulting sentences in the box of the original sentence.</li> \n\t<li>To <b>delete a sentence</b>, leave its box empty.</li>\n</ul>\nMake all changes you find appropriate before proceeding with the survey.<br><br>"
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691468",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. \n<b>Explain</b> each change you made in the box below each pair.",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "explain_c5",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691468",
                "QuestionType": "TE",
                "Selector": "ML",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. Explain each change you...",
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "ForceResponse": "OFF",
                        "ForceResponseType": "ON",
                        "Type": "None",
                        "MinChars": "1"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "SearchSource": {
                    "AllowFreeResponse": "false"
                },
                "QuestionJS": "// ----------\n// HELPER FUNCS\n// ----------\n\n// --- word-level diffs helper ---\nfunction wordDiff(orig, edited) {\n    // tokenize: split into words; punctuation treated as separate tokens\n    function tokenize(str) {\n        return str.match(/[a-zA-Z0-9']+|[^a-zA-Z0-9'\\s]/g) || []\n    }\n\n    var origWords = tokenize(orig)\n    var editedWords = tokenize(edited)\n    var result = document.createDocumentFragment() // build diffs display in a fragment to be inserted into the DOM at once\n    // fragment is iteratively built from <span> elements\n\n    var m = origWords.length,\n        n = editedWords.length\n    var dp = [] // dynamic programming table\n\n    // initialize dp table\n    for (var i = 0; i <= m; i++) {\n        dp[i] = []\n        for (var j = 0; j <= n; j++) dp[i][j] = 0\n    }\n\n    // compute longest common subsequence length\n    // iterate over original (i) and edited (j) sentences, word by word\n    for (var i = 1; i <= m; i++)\n        for (var j = 1; j <= n; j++)\n            // fill dp table\n            dp[i][j] =\n                // note: dp[1][1] corresp to origWords[0] vs editedWords[0] => hence -1 offset\n                origWords[i - 1] === editedWords[j - 1] // test match\n                    ? dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1 // if match => extend LCS count by 1\n                    : Math.max(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1]) // if no match => take max achievable LCS by removing from orig or edited\n\n    // backtrack to find and store edit operations (keep/add/remove)\n    var ops = [],\n        // start from end of table\n        i = m,\n        j = n\n    while (i > 0 || j > 0) {\n        // \"keep\" if i and j words at current position match\n        if (i > 0 && j > 0 && origWords[i - 1] === editedWords[j - 1]) {\n            // prepend <span> for kept word\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"keep\", word: editedWords[j - 1] })\n            i--\n            j--\n            // \"add\" if no match and j word has no i counterpart (move left)\n            // prefer add over remove if tie in LCS length (arbitrary choice)\n        } else if (j > 0 && (i === 0 || dp[i][j - 1] >= dp[i - 1][j])) {\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"add\", word: editedWords[j - 1] })\n            j--\n        } else {\n            // \"remove\" if no match and i word has no j counterpart (move up)\n            ops.unshift({ type: \"remove\", word: origWords[i - 1] })\n            i--\n        }\n    }\n\n    // apply stored edit operations to build final diff display\n    ops.forEach(function (op, k) {\n        // create a <span> for each word (word-level operation) and style according to operation type\n        var span = document.createElement(\"span\")\n        // test if word is punctuation\n        var isPunct = /^[^a-zA-Z0-9']$/.test(op.word)\n        // remove whitespace from start/end of punctuation tokens to avoid weird spacing in the diff display but keep spacing for regular words\n        span.textContent = (k > 0 && !isPunct ? \" \" : \"\") + op.word\n        // style <span> according to operation type\n        if (op.type === \"add\") {\n            span.className = \"diff-add\"\n        } else if (op.type === \"remove\") {\n            span.className = \"diff-remove\"\n        }\n        result.appendChild(span)\n    })\n\n    return result\n}\n\n// --- answer validation ---\nfunction isValidExplanation(text) {\n    var trimmed = text.trim()\n\n    // min 8 characters\n    if (trimmed.length < 8) return false\n\n    // min 2 words\n    var words = trimmed.split(/\\s+/).filter(function (w) {\n        return w.length > 0\n    })\n    if (words.length < 2) return false\n\n    // min 2 distinct words\n    var lower = words.map(function (w) {\n        return w.toLowerCase()\n    })\n    var unique = lower.filter(function (w, i) {\n        return lower.indexOf(w) === i\n    })\n    if (unique.length < 2) return false\n\n    // min 1 vowel\n    if (!/[aeiouAEIOU]/.test(trimmed)) return false\n\n    // less than half of all characters are digits\n    var digitCount = (trimmed.match(/[0-9]/g) || []).length\n    if (digitCount > trimmed.length / 2) return false\n\n    return true\n}\n\nfunction saveExplanations() {\n    var explanations = []\n    document.querySelectorAll(\".explanationBox\").forEach(function (box) {\n        explanations.push({\n            index: parseInt(box.dataset.index, 10),\n            explanation: box.value.trim(),\n        })\n    })\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\n        \"EditExplanationsJSON\",\n        // JSON.stringify(explanations),\n        btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(explanations)))),\n    )\n}\n\n// ----------\n// GLOBAL VARS\n// ----------\nvar qContainer\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function () {\n    // get question container\n    qContainer = this.getQuestionContainer()\n\n    // get raw sentence pairs from embedded data\n    var rawSentencePairs = \"${e://Field/EditPairsJSON}\"\n\n    // decode and parse pairs from JSON\n    var pairs\n    var json = decodeURIComponent(escape(atob(rawSentencePairs)))\n    pairs = JSON.parse(json)\n\n    // --- display ---\n    // hide default Qualtrics text box\n    var defaultInput = qContainer.querySelector(\"textarea\")\n    defaultInput.style.display = \"none\"\n\n    // create main container as div\n    var container = document.createElement(\"div\")\n    defaultInput.parentNode.appendChild(container)\n\n    // render one block per sentence pair\n    pairs.forEach(function (pair, idx) {\n        var wrapper = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        wrapper.className = \"card\"\n\n        // header\n        var header = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        header.className = \"card-label\"\n        header.textContent = \"Sentence \" + (idx + 1)\n        wrapper.appendChild(header)\n\n        // original sentence\n        var origDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origDiv.className = \"sentence_block-orig\"\n        var origStrong = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        origStrong.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label sentence_type-label--original\"\n        origStrong.textContent = \"Original\"\n        origDiv.appendChild(origStrong)\n        origDiv.appendChild(document.createTextNode(pair.orig))\n        wrapper.appendChild(origDiv)\n\n        // submitted sentence\n        var editedDiv = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        // check edits were made => to determine display style + whether to attach explanation box\n        var isModified = pair.orig !== pair.edited\n        editedDiv.className =\n            \"sentence_block-edit\" +\n            (isModified ? \" sentence_block-edit--modified\" : \"\")\n        var editedStrong = document.createElement(\"div\")\n        editedStrong.className =\n            \"sentence_type-label \" +\n            (isModified\n                ? \"sentence_type-label--edit\"\n                : \"sentence_type-label--original\")\n        // label\n        editedStrong.textContent = isModified ? \"Your edit\" : \"Unchanged\"\n        editedDiv.appendChild(editedStrong)\n        editedDiv.appendChild(wordDiff(pair.orig, pair.edited))\n        wrapper.appendChild(editedDiv)\n\n        // explanation prompt + text box only if modified\n        if (isModified) {\n            var label = document.createElement(\"div\")\n            label.className = \"explanation-label\"\n            label.textContent = \"Why did you make this/these change(s)?\"\n            wrapper.appendChild(label)\n\n            var explanationBox = document.createElement(\"textarea\")\n            explanationBox.rows = 3\n            explanationBox.className = \"explanation-textarea explanationBox\"\n            explanationBox.dataset.index = idx\n            wrapper.appendChild(explanationBox)\n        }\n\n        container.appendChild(wrapper)\n    })\n\n    // --- require all & valid explanations ---\n    var nextBtn = document.getElementById(\"NextButton\")\n\n    if (nextBtn) {\n        // next-click listener\n        nextBtn.addEventListener(\n            \"click\",\n            function (e) {\n                var boxes = document.querySelectorAll(\".explanationBox\")\n                var allFilled = true\n                var firstInvalidBox = null // keep track of the first invalid box to jump back to if needed\n\n                boxes.forEach(function (box) {\n                    box.style.border = \"1px solid #ddd\"\n                    var errorMsg =\n                        box.parentNode.querySelector(\".explanationError\")\n                    if (errorMsg) errorMsg.remove()\n\n                    // check validity of explanation text\n                    if (!isValidExplanation(box.value)) {\n                        allFilled = false\n                        box.style.border = \"1px solid #e57373\"\n                        var error = document.createElement(\"div\")\n                        error.className = \"explanationError explanation-error\"\n                        error.textContent =\n                            \"Please explain why you made this change.\"\n                        box.parentNode.insertBefore(error, box.nextSibling)\n                        if (!firstInvalidBox) firstInvalidBox = box\n                    }\n                })\n\n                // if invalid or incomplete answers, scroll to first problematic box\n                if (!allFilled) {\n                    e.stopImmediatePropagation()\n                    e.preventDefault()\n                    firstInvalidBox.scrollIntoView({\n                        behavior: \"smooth\",\n                        block: \"center\",\n                    })\n                    firstInvalidBox.focus()\n                } else {\n                    // if all validly filled, save explanations\n                    saveExplanations()\n                }\n            },\n            true,\n        )\n    } else {\n        console.log(\"NextButton not found\")\n    }\n})\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnPageSubmit(function () {\n    // fallback save in case addOnPageSubmit fires without going through the click handler\n    // note: then explanations are not validated\n    saveExplanations()\n})",
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Below you can find each original sentence alongside your edited version. <b>Explain</b> each change you made in the box below each pair."
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
            "Element": "SQ",
            "PrimaryAttribute": "QID1219691469",
            "SecondaryAttribute": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation. As part of a group project, your team has t...",
            "TertiaryAttribute": null,
            "Payload": {
                "QuestionText": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team has to submit a 200-word news article and\nyour teammate, Brandon, is in charge of writing it. To do so, he used the newest\nLLM, designed to have a very human-like writing style.\n<br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor actively tracks new\ndevelopments in LLMs and has already cautioned against their use in coursework.\nYou are worried he will suspect the article was produced with the help of an\nLLM, which would penalize the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is therefore to edit the text so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this new LLM, you first generate\ntwo sample articles using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Example 1</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">The mystery of disappearing Chinese tycoons</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>In recent years, many of China\u2019s business leaders have disappeared from public view. Rumours are spreading about the forces reshaping the country\u2019s corporate elite. Well-known real estate developers, technology pioneers, and other executives have been forced to step down. They've vanished from social media and some have even been detained without explanation.</p>\n           <p>Analysts believe Beijing\u2019s anti-corruption campaigns and regulatory crackdowns as the key reason. The authorities have tightened oversight in sectors including property development, technology, and finance, over concerns of systemic risk and national security. In several high-profile cases, the executives who disappeared later returned to acknowledge investigations into alleged financial crimes or regulatory violations. While some have faced formal charges, a few have remained under the radar.</p>\n           <p>With investment risk having increased, so have questions about transparency in the world's second largest economy. The international markets have reacted badly to the sudden drop in leadership from major firms. This has demonstrated the importance of China's policies around the world.</p>\n           <p>Chinese officials claim that the investigations into these executives are necessary to promote \"a common prosperity among people\" and to ensure long-term stability. This pattern has highlighted the balance between private enterprise and state authority in Modern China.</p></div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Example 2</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">A look at the physical tests needed to be a firefighter</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>Firefighting is a physically demanding profession, and most departments require candidates to pass rigorous physical tests before becoming a firefighter. Recruits must pass exams that simulate real-life emergencies.</p>\n           <p>The typical Candidate Physical Ability Test (CPAT) includes eight timed events. Applicants must climb stairs while carrying weighted equipment, dragging charged hoses across a set distance, and raise and extend heavy ladders. Training requires applicants to  pass forcible entry simulations, using weighted sleds though dark, confined spaces to rescue a mannequin.</p>\n           <p>Strength, endurance, agility, and cardiovascular fitness are measured during the evaluation. Candidates wear a weighted vest to replicate a firefighter's protective gear. The test must be completed within10 minutes, to prove both speed and stamina.</p>\n           <p>Meeting these standards is essential for firefighters to be able to protect the public. Failure rates are high. Anyone considering a career as a firefighter should build their abilities with strength training and aerobic conditioning to prepare for the tests.</p></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n<br />\nWith these examples in mind, you now turn to\n<strong>Brandon's text</strong> below. It will be shown again on the next page\nwith space to make your edits. <br /><br />\n\n<div>\n    <div class=\"card\">\n        <div class=\"card-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-title\">Weird and wonderful Christmas traditions across Europe</div>\n        <div class=\"stimulus-body\">   <p>From churchgoers in Venezuela who roller skate, to children in Germany who throw shoes. Every December Europe is nice place with traditions that sound little strange for Americans but, nonetheless are cherished by various countries in Europe. In Catalonia, Spain the Caga Ti\u00f3 is a log that is placed in the house and fed for weeks before Christmas. On Christmas Eve, children beat the log with sticks while singing, and waiting and hoping for it to produce for the eager children sweets and small gifts.</p>\n           <p>The festive season in Austria and parts of southern Germany is not celebrated in the same way as other countries, it is dark and eerie, not as warm or bright and just a little creepy. Men dressed as horned Krampus creatures walk through town squares, rattling chains and playfully chasing children and other fun-loving spectators, reviving a centuries old Alpine legend meant to frighten naughty children.</p>\n           <p>In Ukraine, Christmas tree is illuminated with fake spider webs, inspired by a legend in which spiders spun silver threads to help a poor family celebrate their Christmases. Households in Norway tend to hide their brooms on Christmas Eve to prevent mischievous and naughty spirits said to fly in the sky during the night.</p>\n           <p>These bizarre traditions showcase Europe\u2019s rich history of folklore, faith and fun, reminding visitors that the magic of Christmas often lies in the delightfully unexpected places. From Italy\u2019s gift bearing witch La Befana to the Czech custom of tossing shoes to predict marriage, the continent embraces the joys of Christmas celebrations in this festive winter season.</p></div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n",
                "DefaultChoices": false,
                "DataExportTag": "instruct_c6",
                "QuestionID": "QID1219691469",
                "QuestionType": "DB",
                "Selector": "TB",
                "DataVisibility": {
                    "Private": false,
                    "Hidden": false
                },
                "Configuration": {
                    "QuestionDescriptionOption": "UseText"
                },
                "QuestionDescription": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation. As part of a group project, your team has t...",
                "ChoiceOrder": [],
                "Validation": {
                    "Settings": {
                        "Type": "None"
                    }
                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>In recent years, many of China\u2019s business leaders have disappeared from public view. Rumours are spreading about the forces reshaping the country\u2019s corporate elite. Well-known real estate developers, technology pioneers, and other executives have been forced to step down. They've vanished from social media and some have even been detained without explanation.</p>\n           <p>Analysts believe Beijing\u2019s anti-corruption campaigns and regulatory crackdowns as the key reason. The authorities have tightened oversight in sectors including property development, technology, and finance, over concerns of systemic risk and national security. In several high-profile cases, the executives who disappeared later returned to acknowledge investigations into alleged financial crimes or regulatory violations. While some have faced formal charges, a few have remained under the radar.</p>\n           <p>With investment risk having increased, so have questions about transparency in the world's second largest economy. The international markets have reacted badly to the sudden drop in leadership from major firms. This has demonstrated the importance of China's policies around the world.</p>\n           <p>Chinese officials claim that the investigations into these executives are necessary to promote \"a common prosperity among people\" and to ensure long-term stability. This pattern has highlighted the balance between private enterprise and state authority in Modern China.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Firefighting is a physically demanding profession, and most departments require candidates to pass rigorous physical tests before becoming a firefighter. Recruits must pass exams that simulate real-life emergencies.</p>\n           <p>The typical Candidate Physical Ability Test (CPAT) includes eight timed events. Applicants must climb stairs while carrying weighted equipment, dragging charged hoses across a set distance, and raise and extend heavy ladders. Training requires applicants to  pass forcible entry simulations, using weighted sleds though dark, confined spaces to rescue a mannequin.</p>\n           <p>Strength, endurance, agility, and cardiovascular fitness are measured during the evaluation. Candidates wear a weighted vest to replicate a firefighter's protective gear. The test must be completed within10 minutes, to prove both speed and stamina.</p>\n           <p>Meeting these standards is essential for firefighters to be able to protect the public. Failure rates are high. Anyone considering a career as a firefighter should build their abilities with strength training and aerobic conditioning to prepare for the tests.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>From churchgoers in Venezuela who roller skate, to children in Germany who throw shoes. Every December Europe is nice place with traditions that sound little strange for Americans but, nonetheless are cherished by various countries in Europe. In Catalonia, Spain the Caga Ti\u00f3 is a log that is placed in the house and fed for weeks before Christmas. On Christmas Eve, children beat the log with sticks while singing, and waiting and hoping for it to produce for the eager children sweets and small gifts.</p>\n           <p>The festive season in Austria and parts of southern Germany is not celebrated in the same way as other countries, it is dark and eerie, not as warm or bright and just a little creepy. Men dressed as horned Krampus creatures walk through town squares, rattling chains and playfully chasing children and other fun-loving spectators, reviving a centuries old Alpine legend meant to frighten naughty children.</p>\n           <p>In Ukraine, Christmas tree is illuminated with fake spider webs, inspired by a legend in which spiders spun silver threads to help a poor family celebrate their Christmases. Households in Norway tend to hide their brooms on Christmas Eve to prevent mischievous and naughty spirits said to fly in the sky during the night.</p>\n           <p>These bizarre traditions showcase Europe\u2019s rich history of folklore, faith and fun, reminding visitors that the magic of Christmas often lies in the delightfully unexpected places. From Italy\u2019s gift bearing witch La Befana to the Czech custom of tossing shoes to predict marriage, the continent embraces the joys of Christmas celebrations in this festive winter season.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
