                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>An increasing number of companies have been migrating to cloud computing platforms. New research suggests that a major driver of this is FOMO or \"fear of missing out.\" According to a recent industry survey, 81% of business leaders say that their organization's investments in cloud infrastructure are influenced by FOMO on innovation, competitive advantage, and industry momentum.</p>\n           <p>The benefits of cloud adoption that are usually preferred are cost savings, scalability, and flexibility but studies indicate that competition also plays an equally powerful role. Executives are compelled to modernize IT systems as their rivals are adopting AI tools, data analytics platforms, and remote collaboration technologies built on cloud infrastructure.</p>\n           <p>Analysts say FOMO reflects a broader shift in corporate strategy. As opposed to waiting for clear returns on investment, companies are now being proactive to avoid falling behind their competitors. Cloud adoption is viewed as essential for digital transformation in sectors like finance, retail, and healthcare. It is assumed that rushed migrations can create new risks such as cybersecurity vulnerabilities and spiraling costs.</p>\n           <p>The cloud has become less of a technical upgrade and more of a strategic necessity driven more by perception and pressure rather than by measurable gains.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>From churchgoers in Venezuela who roller skate, to children in Germany who throw shoes. Every December Europe is nice place with traditions that sound little strange for Americans but, nonetheless are cherished by various countries in Europe. In Catalonia, Spain the Caga Ti\u00f3 is a log that is placed in the house and fed for weeks before Christmas. On Christmas Eve, children beat the log with sticks while singing, and waiting and hoping for it to produce for the eager children sweets and small gifts.</p>\n           <p>The festive season in Austria and parts of southern Germany is not celebrated in the same way as other countries, it is dark and eerie, not as warm or bright and just a little creepy. Men dressed as horned Krampus creatures walk through town squares, rattling chains and playfully chasing children and other fun-loving spectators, reviving a centuries old Alpine legend meant to frighten naughty children.</p>\n           <p>In Ukraine, Christmas tree is illuminated with fake spider webs, inspired by a legend in which spiders spun silver threads to help a poor family celebrate their Christmases. Households in Norway tend to hide their brooms on Christmas Eve to prevent mischievous and naughty spirits said to fly in the sky during the night.</p>\n           <p>These bizarre traditions showcase Europe\u2019s rich history of folklore, faith and fun, reminding visitors that the magic of Christmas often lies in the delightfully unexpected places. From Italy\u2019s gift bearing witch La Befana to the Czech custom of tossing shoes to predict marriage, the continent embraces the joys of Christmas celebrations in this festive winter season.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>The 30th May marks an important milestone in WMNO\u2019s history, showing the many positive changes that have taken place at WMMO over the years.  WMMO moved to a fully classic rock format in 1985, kicking things off with a track from the Rolling Stones.  The debut song that morning \u201cStart Me Up\u201d sparked a new era that Central Florida audiences quickly related to.</p>\n           <p>Then in 1999, WMMO rolled out its annual Memorial Weekend Rock Marathon, a now staple time in the history of the brand. This gave fans 48 hours of classic rock with barely any interruptions.</p>\n           <p>In 2012, WMMO launched its revamped mobile app to keep up with the moderising world, connecting a whole new generation of digital listeners with exclusive backstage interviews and live concert streams. This colloborated the modern day culture of music whilst preserving WMNO's commirtment to its fans.</p>\n           <p>With all of the above in mind May 30th is a testement to WNMO's lifelong dedication to it's audience going above and beyond in the services and experiences they provide to fans.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
