                },
                "GradingData": [],
                "Language": [],
                "NextChoiceId": 4,
                "NextAnswerId": 1,
                "QuestionText_Unsafe": "Imagine you find yourself in the following situation.<br /><br />\n\nAs part of a group project, your team is required to submit a 200-word essay.\nYour teammate, Brandon, is responsible for writing this essay. He sent you his\ndraft, but also admitted that he used an LLM to generate it. He tried assuring\nyou that the LLM he used is a new one, designed to have a very human-like\nwriting style. <br /><br />\n\nHowever, this puts your group at risk. Your professor has expressed concerns\nabout students using LLMs to complete assignments. You don't want to make your\nprofessor suspicious and you are worried that Brandon's essay could be\nidentified as AI-generated, which would negatively affect the entire group.\n<br /><br />\n\n<strong>Your task</strong> is to edit Brandon's essay so that it reads\nconvincingly as human-written and is unlikely to be identified as LLM-generated.\n<br /><br />\n\nTo get a better sense of the writing style of this LLM, you first generate three\nsample essays using it. They are shown below.<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_1_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_1_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Jimmy Wales, who co founded Wikipedia 25 years ago, has said the online encyclopedia needs a big overhaul and that blockchain technology could be the change thats needed. At a recent tech conference, Wales said that Wikipedia's volunteer driven model has been struggling with alot of issues including less editors taking part, disputes over governance, and growing mistrust about content moderation.</p>\n           <p>In his proposal, articles and edits would be put onto a public blockchain. This would create a see through history of everyone who has contributed. He said members of the public could become contributors to the program and earn digital tokens for edits that are verified, with the hope of attracting experts from the specific field. Mr Wales believes that \"smart\" contracts might be useful in creating a platform that is more well rounded.</p>\n           <p>Wales is hoping his plans would make the site harder to manipulate and that by giving power to a wider group of people, complaints about the current administrator groups will be reduced. People who are critical of his ideas are not convinced that blockchain systems can be scaled up to handle Wikipedia's popularity, and suggest that token incentives might encourge low quality edits.</p>\n           <p>The Wikimedia Foundation said it was always interested in new ideas, but that staying non profit and embracing its community is the key thing. The future of Wikipedia seems to be unknown. We can only wait and see if it can reinvent itself while still remaining a trusted brand.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_2_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_2_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t   <p>Beijing Dance Academy has a vast history full of well known, talented intructors and dancers who have left their echoes as reminders within its marble corridors, along with calligraphy scrolls and framed production images from historic ballets. Founded in 1954, the institution is well known for hostin China\u2019s best ballet and classical dancers, who are known for their skills in blending Russian-inspired technique with the traditional Chinese aesthetic. in 1945 the institution well known as the venue of Chinas best ballet and classical dancers was founded. the russian inspired technique was blended with the chinease aesthetic</p>\n           <p>as young as eleven years old, dancers start balancing academic studies with their hours of rehearsals. teachers acemphasize discipline, precision, and emotional expression, using their previous prinicipal dancer experience to teach new generations. \u201cTechnique is only the beginning,\u201d. Li Xinyue, a senior instructor at the institution states \u201cWe try teach our students here to tell stories that resonate beyond borders.\u201d.</p>\n           <p>with recent graduating students joining leading companies in places like, Shanghai, London, and New York.The prestigious nature of the school has spread wide,</p>\n           <p>because of this growing internation reach, competition for a place is vigourus . Each year, thousands of students audition for the chance to attend, driven by goals of following their potential teachers footsteps and becoming principal dancers. the Beijing Dance Academy stands as both a symbol and training ground of artistic ambition and expression. Administrators say new scholarships aim to increase access for rural and low income applicants next year as they continue to update reforms.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">__PRIME_3_LABEL__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__PRIME_3_TOPIC__</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n\t\t\t__PRIME_3_PARAGRAPHS_HTML__\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n\t\n<br />\nWith these samples in mind, you now turn to <strong>Brandon's essay</strong>:\n<br /><br />\n\n<div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-card\">\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-label\">Brandon's essay</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-title\">__STIMULUS_TOPIC__</div>\n\t<div class=\"stimulus-body\">\n           <p>Scientists have discovered a prehistoric worm like creature which they describe as \u201cstrange beyond measure,\u201d this finding shows an unusual branch of early animal evolution. Fossilized remains were found in 520 million year old marine sediments in China. The creatures revealed a soft bodied organism with a tubular form, ringed segments, and a circular mouth lined with sharp spines.</p>\n           <p>The creature measured just a few inches long, and it most likely lived on the seafloor during the Cambrian Period. Researchers believe the creature used its spiny mouth to latch onto prey or organic material, drawing food into a simple digestive tract and obtaining needed nutrients. The creature has an incredibly unique anatomy.</p>\n           <p>Lead paleontologist Dr. Li Wen said, \u201cIt\u2019s strange beyond measure\". \u201cIts combination of features doesn\u2019t fit into any known group, living or extinct.\u201d Advanced imaging techniques revealed preserved muscle fibers and traces of internal organs, offering rare insight into soft-bodied animals that rarely are found as fossils.</p>\n           <p>The discovery suggests early marine ecosystems were more diverse than we originally thought. Scientists hope more study will clarify where this creature fits in evolution, and what it reveals about the past.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>\n",
                "QuestionJS": false
            }
        },
        {
            "SurveyID": "SV_cwM3MQomjAv0nJA",
